The paper proposes a novel formulation for category-level manipulation using semantic 3D keypoints as the object representation. This involves leveraging advances in instance segmentation, 3D keypoint detection, optimization-based robot action planning, and local dense-geometry-based action execution. These topics are all related to robotics and computer vision, which are typically covered in the cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization-based planning and execution, which could also fall under the cs.LG sub-category. Finally, the paper involves hardware experiments, which could fall under the cs.SY sub-category.
